Published Sunday, 2026-03-29, including PRs merged Friday, 2026-03-06 through Thursday, 2026-03-12.
壷@fc9714bc19169eec75cb71fe16b798fac0b6508dc19467f69f438ea2f6af1c6fﾚﾋTitle: title: 'This week in Nushell #342'
Path: Nushell
Content:
@Juhan280:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17785] updated reedline to commit 5c2f105 (#17785)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17749] refactored the display logic for 
``ReedlineEvent``
 and 
``EditCommand``
 to nushell (#17749)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17747] added ToStart/ToEnd reedline events (#17747)
@Bahex:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17782] made 
``Span``
's 
``Debug``
 impl succinct (#17782)
@fdncred:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17781] added support for parsing 
``hh:mm:ss``
 formatted strings in 
``into duration``
 (#17781)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17779] updated dependencies and improved compatibility (#17779)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17759] added 'document' flag to parse HTML as a full document in 
``query_web``
 (#17759)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17737] fixed select pushdown column aliasing (#17737)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17734] updated Rust version to 1.92.0 and fixed clippy warnings in configuration (#17734)
@pickx:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17777] fixed format strings with tokens after ending quote (#17777)
@weirdan:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17775] preserved metadata in 
``reject``
 (#17775)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17762] added 
``char``
 completions (#17762)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17761] added 
``ansi``
 completions (#17761)
@cptpiepmatz:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17767] refactored most nested command integration tests in 
``nu-command``
 (#17767)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17766] merged 
``To/FromYaml``
 and 
``To/FromYml``
 into one struct (#17766)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17765] bumped some packages to handle security issues (#17765)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17750] added 
``TestResult::expect_value_eq``
 and improved 
``test()``
 errors (#17750)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17748] used 
``std::panic::Location``
 instead of custom 
``Location``
 type (#17748)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17745] updated more tests and used 
``assert_contains()``
 (#17745)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17742] bumped aws related crates (#17742)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17740] moved some tests around and applied more 
``nu_test_support::test``
 (#17740)
@WindSoilder:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17764] fixed pipefail behavior with 
``try``
, 
``catch``
, and 
``finally``
 (#17764)
@0xRozier:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17753] allowed passing null to optional positional params in builtin commands (#17753)
@preiter93:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17752] bumped edtui to 0.11.2 and removed workarounds in nu-explore (#17752)
@Jaredw2289-svg:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17751] improved alias expression error message with user-friendly descriptions (#17751)
@Bortlesboat:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17746] fixed confusing type mismatch error in bytes collect (#17746)
@coravacav:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17744] fixed input listen timeout calculation (#17744)
@blindFS:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17741] moved reserved variable name checking near 
``is_variable``
 and 
``add_variable``
 (#17741)
@app/dependabot:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17772] bumped calamine from 0.33.0 to 0.34.0 (#17772)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/17771] bumped quickcheck_macros from 1.1.0 to 1.2.0 (#17771)
